1 Section 2. Section 2-15-143, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "2-15-143. Training and consultationConsultation and training -- duties of tribal liaison --
3 reporting. (1) When establishing a government-to-government relationship with tribal governments, a state
4 agency shall:
5 (a) collaborate with tribal governments in the development of policies, agreements, administrative
6 rules, and program implementation that directly affect Indian tribes;
7 (b) consult with tribal governments as often as is required to address matters that have tribal
8 implications;
9 (c) develop a written consultation policy in coordination with representatives of each federally
10 recognized tribe in the state that is used by the agency for issues involving specific Indian tribes. A consultation
11 policy must be created by January 1, 2026, and be updated as often as required to facilitate timely and
12 meaningful consultation, but no less than biannually.
13 (d) provide tribal governments in the state with a copy of the agency's initial consultation policy and
14 all subsequent updates to the policy;
15 (e) designate an agency employee to act as a tribal liaison who reports directly to the head of the
16 state agency; and
17 (f) ensure that a tribal liaison receives regular trainings that assist in the liaison's job functions,
18 including but not limited to the training prescribed in subsection (4).
19 (2) The position of tribal liaison within a state agency is responsible for:
20 (a) assisting the state agency in developing and implementing state and agency policies that
21 promote effective communication and collaboration between the state agency and tribal governments;
22 (b) serving as a contact person with tribal governments and maintaining communication between
23 the state agency and affected tribal governments; and
24 (c) coordinating training of state agency employees in government-to-government relations that
25 includes at a minimum:
26 (i) effective communication and collaboration between state agencies and Indian tribes; and
27 (ii) cultural competency in providing effective services to tribal governments and tribal members.
